profile.title: DDS
profile.bio:
Dr. Frank Hsu has been practicing dentistry for over ten years and in San Carlos since 2003. Dr. Hsu completed the Advanced Education in General Dentistry Program, a post-doctoral residency at the University of California, San Francisco, earned his DDS from Northwestern University, and his undergraduate degree from Berkeley. During his days off from work, Dr. Hsu enjoys traveling, playing tennis, and spending time with his family. Dr. Hsu and his wife reside in Belmont with their two children, Conrad and Naomi. 

Dr. Hsu has committed to serve the community with the most updated clinical skills and the highest quality of dental care. The services offered with emphasis in preventive care, general dentistry, and cosmetic dentistry. He takes continuing education classes to learn and implement advance technology to provide his patients with the best quality of care. Dr. Hsu is certified with Lumineers, BioLase, Conscious Sedation, and Oral Implantology. Additionally, his staff participates in some of the continuing education courses to increases their skills and education. 

Dr. Hsu is a member of: American Dental Association, California Dental Association, Academy of General Dentistry, San Mateo Dental Society, International Congress of Oral Implantology, and World Laser Institute.

practices.description:
Fairfield dentists Frank Chen, DDS and Judy Su, DDS, and the entire staff of Solano Dental Group, welcome you the website of our Fairfield, CA family and cosmetic dental practice. We hope your visit today is the first step you take toward your best oral health. 

Whether you’re here to learn more about our Fairfield dental office, browse our cosmetic dentistry treatments, or to research a dental procedure you might be interested in, we would be happy to discuss your treatment goals and help you achieve your best smile. Contact us today, or simply request an appointment on our website if you would like us to create a roadmap to your dream smile. 

If you’re trying to find a family or cosmetic dentist in Fairfield, CA, we know the search can be difficult. You need to find a Fairfield dentist you can trust and feel comfortable with. Rather than tell you all of the reasons you should come see us, we would like to highlight what sets us apart and let you decide if we’re the right family and cosmetic dentist in Fairfield for you.

profile.title: DDS
profile.bio:
Dr. Chen attended the Massachusetts Institute of Technology and earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Electrical Engineering in 1993. After completing his undergraduate studies, he chose to pursue a career in dentistry and earned a Doctor of Dental Surgery degree from the prestigious University of California, San Francisco School of Dentistry. Dr. Chen has completed dental implant training at the WhiteCap Institute and is certified in Laser and Oral Sedation Dentistry. 

Dr. Chen Co-founded Solano Dental Group in 2001 and has built a successful practice by providing the highest standard of care to his patients. Patient satisfaction is always his top priority. Dr. Chen is also a member of Parkside Dental Group (www.parksidedental.com), a multi-specialty dental team that provides specialty care in areas of: 

Children's Dentistry 
Cosmetic Dentistry 
Endodontics (root canal therapy) 
Oral Surgery 
Orthodontics 

Outside of work, Dr. Chen enjoys spending time with his family. He enjoys traveling, rock climbing, scuba diving, and skiing. He is also a yoga enthusiast.

profile.title: MD
profile.bio:
I was born in New York, but grew up in Charlottesville, Virginia. After going back to the northeast for college (Yale) and medical school (Columbia) I moved to California.  After medical school, I trained first in Internal Medicine, a specialty I choose because of its complexity, and vast knowledge base. However, shortly after finishing my residency I became interested in Emergency Medicine with its healthy mix of difficult diagnoses, rare diseases and procedural interventions. I then went back to complete a second residency in Emergency Medicine at UCLA.

Within Emergency Medicine, there are a couple of areas that grabbed my interest, the first of which goes by the phrase “evidence-based medicine”. Did you know that most medical diagnosis is based on probability, not certainty? Evidence-based medicine (EBM) attempts to quantify everything that can be quantitated within clinical medicine. The quantitative aspects of EBM drew me into medical computing, the next area of interest I’ll share with you. Over a period of several years I learned numerous computer programming and scripting languages in order to work on a number of a variety of interesting medical computing projects.

I’ve worked in a number of diverse emergency medicine environments. I have extensive experience in trauma care and all areas of Emergency Medicine from my prior work at UCLA Medical Center, Grady Memorial Hospital (Atlanta), San Francisco General Hospital, and Stanford to name a few. I actually had worked part time at Kaiser Permanente Redwood City Emergency Department for a number of years before joining full time as an associate physician. I find that it’s easier to provide a high quality of care in the Kaiser Permanente environment to a large extent because of the integration of care. I also think that the Kaiser Permanente system will have a growing advantage over other area hospitals because of the use of technology to improve care, and that fits perfectly with my interests in EBM and medical informatics.

practices.name: El Camino Urology
practices.description:
El Camino Urology Medical Group, Inc is a single specialty urology practice started over 40 years ago. We have recently relocated to the Melchor Pavilion (formerly Cypress Pavilion), a newly constructed office building across the street from El Camino Hospital. Our contemporary office space is specifically designed to accommodate the modern urology practice. The physicians of ECUMG, Inc are all trained in the specialty of urology. Our physicians are specifically trained to take care of the entire spectrum of urologic problems encountered and they are dedicated to providing the best urologic care for their patients.

We offer our patients the convenience of a CLIA certified lab in our office directly under the supervision of our physicians. This allows for a fast, reliable and efficient method for getting lab results to our patients.

We perform surgery at and admit patients to El Camino Hospital which has been given numerous local and national awards for excellence in nursing care. In fact, El Camino Hospital is the only hospital in the San Francisco Bay Area and one of only six in California to receive Magnet® designation by the American Nurses Credentialing Center (ANCC).

profile.title: MD
profile.bio: Frank C. Lai, MD is a board certified urologist who has been with the El Camino Urology Medical Group since 2003. He was born in Taiwan and raised in Chicago; there he attended the Illinois Mathematics and Science Academy. He is a Phi Beta Kappa graduate of Johns Hopkins University where he was the Conference Champion. Dr. Lai earned his medical degree from Northwestern University Medical School where he was elected to the Alpha Omega Alpha Honor Medical Society. He completed his residency and served as a Chief Resident in urology at Stanford University where he received several awards for his research and publications. He went on to complete a Society of Laparoendoscopic Surgeons certified Minimally Invasive Surgery fellowship at Cedars Sinai Medical Center. There he specialized in advanced, minimally invasive laparoscopic, robotic, and endoscopic procedures for a variety of urologic conditions including kidney, adrenal, and prostate cancers, complex stone diseases, and voiding dysfunction. He is also particularly interested in the medical management and prevention of stone disease. Dr. Lai is a Fellow of the American College of Surgeons (FACS.
